ink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-7Dr","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":35136,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/02\/01\/prophet-like-a-father\/","url_meta":{"origin":29353,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Cleanliness: The Prophet teaches his companions like a father","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 1, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, I am only like a father to you in the way that I teach you. When one of you goes to relieve himself, he should not face the direction of prayer or turn his back\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":29328,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/13\/concession-urinate-standing\/","url_meta":{"origin":29353,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Cleanliness: Concession to urinate while standing if needed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 13, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Hudhayfah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, came to a waste area used by people and he urinated over it while standing. I brought him water for ablution and then left him to his privacy. The Prophet called me until I was behind him and he performed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13717,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/04\/24\/eat-drink-right-hand\/","url_meta":{"origin":29353,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Manners: Eating and drinking with right hand","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 24, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen one of you eats, let him eat with his right hand. When he drinks, let him drink with his right hand. Verily, the devil eats and drinks with his left hand.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2020\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34037,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/03\/03\/prophet-washes-hands\/","url_meta":{"origin":29353,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hygiene: The Prophet washes his hands before eating","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 3, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, if he wanted to sleep while he was in a state of major ritual impurity, he would perform ablution. If he wanted to eat or drink, he would first wash his hands and then eat or drink. Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":10670,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/12\/24\/husband-wife-ghusl-together\/","url_meta":{"origin":29353,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Bathing: Husband and wife bathing together","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Maymunah, wife of the Prophet, reported: I would take a bath with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, cleaning ourselves of impurities from the same vessel.\u201d Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cIt is the opinion of the majority of jurists, that there is no harm for a husband and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25519,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/wudu-wiping-head-ears\/","url_meta":{"origin":29353,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Wiping head and ears in ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would wipe his head and his ears in ablution, both inner and outer parts. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 39 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Nawawi (\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0633\u064e\u062d\u064e \u0628\u0650\u0631\u064e\u0623\u0652\u0633\u0650\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0623\u064f\u0630\u064f\u0646\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0638\u064e\u0627\u0647\u0650\u0631\u0650\u0647\u0650\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0648\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0627\u0637\u0650\u0646\u0650\u0647\u0650\u0645\u064e\u0627 (\u0641\u064a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/29353","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=29353"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/29353\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=29353"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=29353"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=29353"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}